<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Process of Implementing Improvement Proposals</h3>



<p>The implementation process of improvement proposals plays a crucial role in shaping the evolution of Cardano&#8217;s ecosystem. This process is designed to ensure that the community&#8217;s ideas and suggestions are carefully considered and implemented in a systematic manner.</p>



<p>Here are three key aspects of the process:</p>



<ul>
<li><strong>Voltaire:</strong> Cardano&#8217;s governance model, known as Voltaire, allows ADA holders to propose and vote on improvement proposals. This decentralized approach ensures that decisions are made by the community and reflects the collective interests of stakeholders.</li>



<li><strong>Hackathon: </strong>Cardano organizes hackathons to encourage developers to propose innovative ideas and solutions. These events provide a platform for collaboration and foster creativity within the community.</li>



<li><strong>Hard Fork: </strong>To implement major upgrades, Cardano may undergo a hard fork. This process involves updating the protocol and ledger to accommodate new features and functionalities.</li>
</ul>



